00:00:14.000 --> 00:00:16.000
Today, we are going to make "Green Peas and Mint Soup".

00:00:34.604 --> 00:00:36.604
To make this soup, we require fresh green peas.

00:00:52.550 --> 00:00:54.550
Heat the butter in a non-stick pan.

00:00:53.876 --> 00:00:55.876
Add the finely chopped onions.

00:00:57.326 --> 00:00:59.326
Saute on a medium flame for a few minutes.

00:01:12.703 --> 00:01:14.703
Add the green peas.

00:01:17.118 --> 00:01:19.118
Add 1 1/2 cups of water.

00:01:26.871 --> 00:01:28.871
Add salt to taste.

00:01:30.459 --> 00:01:32.459
Bring to a boil.

00:01:32.345 --> 00:01:34.345
Simmer for 15 minutes or till the peas are cooked.

00:01:43.935 --> 00:01:45.940
Cool and blend in a mixer to a smooth pure and keep aside.

00:01:53.723 --> 00:01:55.720
Take 1/2 cup of water in a broad non-stick pan.

00:01:56.938 --> 00:01:58.940
Add 1/2 cup of milk.

00:02:01.437 --> 00:02:03.440
Add the prepared green pea puree.

00:02:11.759 --> 00:02:13.760
Mix well.

00:02:20.721 --> 00:02:22.720
Add the freshly ground pepper.

00:02:25.282 --> 00:02:27.280
Mix well and cook on a medium flame for 
 3 to 4 minutes, while stirring occasionally.

00:02:29.760 --> 00:02:31.760
Add the chopped mint leaves.

00:02:42.799 --> 00:02:44.800
Serve hot garnished with mint leaves.

